replies.bodyText:
I have examined the master branch head, and I think the replacement rule would be very straightforward:
persistence-api class member functions can be annotated with:
@Cacheable(cacheResolver = "generalRepositoryCacheResolver", condition = "@cacheEnabledConfig.getEnabled()")
in place of
@Cacheable(cacheNames = "GeneralRepositoryCache", condition = "@cacheEnabledConfig.getEnabled()")
This should cover all cases in this PR. There is also a special purpose static repository cache which we are using for holding a small number of items (mainly genes and gene aliases) ... for these functions, the old annotation with cacheNames = "staticRepositoryCacheOne" could be adjusted to use cacheResolver = "staticRepositoryCacheOneResolver" instead ... but I don't think this static cache is relevant to this PR. In fact, the only change that seems to be needed would be in the current file (AlterationRepository.java). The other changes to the API module simply remove functions.

